5 consistent for both nursing facilities and Intermediate Care
6 Facilities for Individuals with Intellectual Disabilities
7 intermediate care facilities for individuals with intellectual
8 disabilities (ICFs/IID).
9 2. The recalculated reimbursement rate shall be implemented
10 September 1, 2000.
11 B. 1. From September 1, 2000, through August 31, 2001, all
12 nursing facilities subject to the Nursing Home Care Act, in addition
13 to other state and federal requirements related to the staffing of
14 nursing facilities, shall maintain the following minimum direct-
15 care-staff-to-resident ratios:
16 a. from 7:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m., one direct-care staff to
17 every eight residents, or major fraction thereof,
18 b. from 3:00 p.m. to 11:00 p.m., one direct-care staff to
19 every twelve residents, or major fraction thereof, and
20 c. from 11:00 p.m. to 7:00 a.m., one direct-care staff to
21 every seventeen residents, or major fraction thereof.
