1 c. from 11:00 p.m. to 7:00 a.m., one direct-care staff to
2 every fifteen residents, or major fraction thereof.
3 4. Effective immediately, facilities shall have the option of
4 varying the starting times for the eight-hour shifts by one (1) hour
5 before or one (1) hour after the times designated in this section
6 without overlapping shifts.
7 5. a. On and after January 1, 2020, a facility may implement
8 twenty-four-hour-based staff scheduling; provided,
9 however, such facility shall continue to maintain a
10 direct-care service rate of at least two and nine
11 tenths nine-tenths (2.9) hours of direct-care service
12 per resident per day, the same to be calculated based
13 on average direct care staff maintained over a twenty-
14 four-hour period.
15 b. At no time shall direct-care staffing ratios in a
16 facility with twenty-four-hour-based staff-scheduling
17 privileges fall below one direct-care staff to every
18 fifteen residents or major fraction thereof, and at
19 least two direct-care staff shall be on duty and awake
20 at all times.
