3 G. For purposes of this subsection section:
4 1. “Direct-care staff” means any nursing or therapy staff who
5 provides direct, hands-on care to residents in a nursing facility;
6 2. Prior to September 1, 2003, activity and social services
7 staff who are not providing direct, hands-on care to residents may
8 be included in the direct-care-staff-to-resident ratio in any shift.
9 On and after September 1, 2003, such persons shall not be included
10 in the direct-care-staff-to-resident ratio, regardless of their
11 licensure or certification status; and
12 3. The administrator shall not be counted in the direct-care-
13 staff-to-resident ratio regardless of the administrator’s licensure
14 or certification status.
15 H. 1. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority shall require all
16 nursing facilities subject to the provisions of the Nursing Home
17 Care Act and Intermediate Care Facilities for Individuals with
18 Intellectual Disabilities intermediate care facilities for
19 individuals with intellectual disabilities (ICFs/IID) with seventeen
20 or more beds to submit a monthly report on staffing ratios on a form
21 that the Authority shall develop.
22 2. The report shall document the extent to which such
23 facilities are meeting or are failing to meet the minimum direct-
24
Req. No. 3985 Page 11

1 care -staff-to-resident ratios specified by this section. Such
2 report shall be available to the public upon request.
3 3. The Authority may assess administrative penalties for the
4 failure of any facility to submit the report as required by the
5 Authority. Provided, however:
6 a. administrative penalties shall not accrue until the
7 Authority notifies the facility in writing that the
8 report was not timely submitted as required, and
9 b. a minimum of a one-day penalty shall be assessed in
10 all instances.
11 4. Administrative penalties shall not be assessed for
12 computational errors made in preparing the report.
13 5. Monies collected from administrative penalties shall be
14 deposited in the Nursing Facility Quality of Care Fund established
15 in Section 2002 of Title 56 of the Oklahoma Statutes and utilized
16 for the purposes specified in the Oklahoma Healthcare Initiative Act
17 such section.
