1 2. a. The Oklahoma Nursing Facility Funding Advisory
2 Committee is hereby created and shall consist of the
3 following:
4 (1) four members selected by the Oklahoma Association
5 of Health Care Providers Care Providers Oklahoma
6 or its successor organization,
7 (2) three members selected by the Oklahoma
8 Association of Homes and Services for the Aging
9 LeadingAge Oklahoma or its successor
10 organization, and
11 (3) two members selected by the State Council on
12 Aging State Council on Aging and Adult Protective
13 Services.
14 The Chair chair shall be elected by the committee. No
15 state employees may be appointed to serve.
16 b. The purpose of the advisory committee will shall be to
17 develop a new methodology for calculating state
18 Medicaid program reimbursements to nursing facilities
19 by implementing facility-specific rates based on
20 expenditures relating to direct care staffing.
21 No nursing home will shall receive less than the
22 current rate at the time of implementation of
23 facility-specific rates pursuant to this subparagraph.
24
Req. No. 3985 Page 13

1 c. The advisory committee shall be staffed and advised by
2 the Oklahoma Health Care Authority.
3 d. The new methodology will shall be submitted for
4 approval to the Board of the Oklahoma Health Care
5 Authority Board by January 15, 2005, and shall be
6 finalized by July 1, 2005. The new methodology will
7 shall apply only to new funds that become available
8 for Medicaid nursing facility reimbursement after the
9 methodology of this paragraph has been finalized.
10 Existing funds paid to nursing homes will shall not be
11 subject to the methodology of this paragraph. The
12 methodology as outlined in this paragraph will shall
13 only be applied to any new funding for nursing
14 facilities appropriated above and beyond the funding
15 amounts effective on January 15, 2005.
16 e. The new methodology shall divide the payment into two
17 components:
18 (1) direct care which includes allowable costs for
19 registered nurses Registered Nurses, licensed
20 practical nurses Licensed Practical Nurses,
21 certified medication aides Certified Medication
22 Aides and certified nurse aides Certified Nurse
23 Aides. The direct care component of the rate
24 shall be a facility-specific rate, directly
Req. No. 3985 Page 14

1 related to each facility’s actual expenditures on
2 direct care, and
3 (2) other costs.
4 f. The Oklahoma Health Care Authority, in calculating the
5 base year prospective direct care rate component,
6 shall use the following criteria:
7 (1) to construct an array of facility per diem
8 allowable expenditures on direct care, the
9 Authority shall use the most recent data
10 available. The limit on this array shall be no
11 less than the ninetieth percentile,
12 (2) each facility’s direct care base-year component
13 of the rate shall be the lesser of the facility’s
14 allowable expenditures on direct care or the
15 limit,
16 (3) other rate components shall be determined by the
17 Oklahoma Nursing Facility Funding Advisory
18 Committee or the Authority in accordance with
19 federal regulations and requirements,
20 (4) prior to July 1, 2020, the Authority shall seek
21 federal approval to calculate the upper payment
22 limit under the authority of CMS the Centers for
23 Medicare and Medicaid Services (CMS) utilizing
24 the Medicare equivalent payment rate, and
